begin_memory_text: We talked about what we did for work and how COVID affected our jobs. We found out that we both are able to work from home. But I have been working from home even prior to COVID.
middle_memory_text: We mostly talked about how COVID had affected our day-to-day lives. How we would get our groceries and how often we leave our house. We talked about how her two kids have been dealing with school during this time.
end_memory_text: We talked about the weather in the states that we lived in and what winter activities are available where we live. I told her that I snowboard at our ski resorts here and she talked about how her and her kids will usually go sledding at a big hill by their school.
rest_of_day_open: I have a regular work week ahead with no planned time off. But once I'm done with work, I will either be doing yoga at the local gym or playing tennis. I will need to go to the store to get something to make food with for the rest of week.
critical_positive: I feel like we were both able to contribute to the conversation equally. There were not any one word answers and we were both able to express how we felt about the topics that were discussed. There were hardly any pauses or down time in the conversation that we had.
critical_negative: I can't think of anything in particular that didn't work in our conversation. Like I mentioned, we both carried the conversation well. We were able to come up with topics to discuss and the time seemed to go by very quickly. The last couple conversations I had were 20 minutes, but this one had to be at least 25 minutes and it didn't feel like any longer.

begin_memory_text: We talked about working from home and what it was like.  My partner had already been working from home so it wasn't much of a change for her.
middle_memory_text: We talked about the pros and cons of working from home, what schedules looked like, the advantages of having a flexible schedule.
end_memory_text: We talked about winter activities (sledding, snowboarding) and Halloween (trick or treating).
rest_of_day_open: I see this week as being really busy.  I have several different meetings and appointments that I don't normally have.  I am excited to see my boyfriend on Thursday as I didn't get to see him last week.  I am a little nervous about a school meeting for my oldest child on Wednesday.
critical_positive: What worked the best was asking my partner about her experiences with working at home.  She didn't offer a lot of specific advice, but it was one thing that we had in common and could agree on.  I was interested in hearing about her experiences, especially with how her workplace transitioned to allowing people to work remotely.
critical_negative: It was kind of hard to keep the conversation going once we realized that we didn't have a lot in common, so I felt that we kept rehashing the same topics - weather, Halloween, working from home.  It was difficult to transition to another subject since we didn't seem to have much in common and I didn't know what the best way to transition to something else would be.
